For each of the {= topic =} business-research topics listed below covering China and Hong Kong satellite manufacturing, identify {= business_signal =}+ public-source business signals per topic, each corroborated by at least {= url =} sources. A proper business signal should be anchored on a concrete entity / factoid piece, e.g. a named manufacturer with a capacity figure, a specific component supplier with output numbers, a named policy with a funding scope, a concrete order or launch batch, or an identified industrial park or HK-Mainland channel arrangement — not a topic label, report title, or generic "the sector is growing" theme.

The purpose is to build a source-bound opportunity map for China and Hong Kong satellite manufacturing, grounded in public verifiable facts, as opposed to private procurement intelligence / investment advice / etc.

Topics:
- `demand_growth`: satellite-industry revenue, LEO constellation buildout, satellite-services growth, remote-sensing or satellite-IoT demand, or application sectors that pull satellite-manufacturing supply
- `manufacturer_capability`: a named China or Hong Kong satellite manufacturer's production capacity, platform range, satellite types, launched-satellite track record, AIT capability, factory qualification, or full-stack delivery capability
- `supply_chain_input`: China or Hong Kong satellite components, payloads, sensors, solar arrays, antennas, propulsion/control subsystems, test equipment, ground systems, terminals, chips, modules, or supplier capacity
- `investment_scale`: facility size, equipment count, production-line capacity, capex, funding, cluster output target, factory phase, or cost-reduction signal that helps size the public investment requirement
- `policy_incentive`: national, provincial, municipal, Hong Kong, or industrial-park policy support for commercial space, satellite manufacturing, launch access, testing assets, procurement, funds, subsidies, talent, or applications
- `customer_commercial_signal`: orders, contracts, launched batches, commercial validation, application customers, service sectors, constellation deployment milestones, or public go-to-market evidence tied to satellite-manufacturing demand
- `hk_mainland_channel`: Hong Kong or Greater Bay Area business channels, listed-company or Science Park manufacturing bases, TT&C/data centers, separate customs or tax/talent advantages, or public Hong Kong-Mainland cooperation that could matter to a cross-border entrant

Substance expectations for provided business signals take different shapes across the topics: for `demand_growth`, demand that pulls satellite-manufacturing supply (LEO buildout, replacement cycles, capacity pressure) rather than downstream service growth without a manufacturing pull; for `manufacturer_capability`, proven capability (launched / qualified / AIT'd track record) rather than announced intent or marketing-language claims; for `supply_chain_input`, production-side delivery evidence (shipped output, in-orbit count, qualification credentials) rather than catalog-style existence claims; for `investment_scale`, entity-bound capital (specific corporate entity / facility / fund) rather than industry-wide aggregates; for `policy_incentive`, a specific instrument (named fund with allocation, program with named participants, decree with scope) rather than stated supportive posture; for `customer_commercial_signal`, contracted commercial commitment (signed orders, deployment milestones, paid pilots) rather than MoUs or strategic-partnership announcements; for `hk_mainland_channel`, an explicit cross-border instrument or HK-anchored corporate channel rather than a Mainland-only operation that happens to source from HK or have HK directors.

The page itself should be of a source class fitting the topic: for `demand_growth`, an industry association, market-research outlet, or sector tracker that publishes demand numbers; for `manufacturer_capability`, a manufacturer-controlled surface or credible third-party industry reporting that names the manufacturer; for `supply_chain_input`, a supplier-controlled surface or component-industry reporting that names the input; for `investment_scale`, an official disclosure (corporate filing, government / industrial-park announcement, or credible business reporting) carrying concrete numbers; for `policy_incentive`, an official policy document or credible reproduction citing the specific instrument; for `customer_commercial_signal`, a primary commercial announcement (press release, contract disclosure, customer-side announcement) naming the order or customer; for `hk_mainland_channel`, an HK-anchored corporate or government source, GBA cooperation framework, or credible cross-border business reporting.

Requirements:
- The page should support the claimed business signal with appropriate precision (particularly, but not exclusively, when it comes to tangible anchors such as named entities / numbers / etc — those should be clearly present on the page, not vaguely implied).
- The page must situate the signal in China or Hong Kong satellite manufacturing — commercial-space policy, satellite components, satellite applications, or a Hong Kong-Mainland business channel — not generic global aerospace or adjacent electronics without a satellite-manufacturing connection.
